# frontend/.dockerignore ‚Äî IN-030 v118 ROOT FIX (Teammate 8)
# =========================================================================
# The root .dockerignore covers the WHOLE repo context, but the
# frontend Dockerfile builds with ``context: .`` (repo root) ‚Äî meaning
# the root .dockerignore applies. This file is for cases where someone
# builds the frontend DIRECTLY from the ``frontend/`` directory:
#
#     cd frontend && docker build -t drugos-frontend .
#
# Without this file, that command sends ``node_modules/`` (~500MB),
# ``.next/`` (~300MB), ``tests/``, ``uploaded_code/``, ``src_backup/``,
# ``prisma_backup/``, ``public_backup/``, ``dev.db``, and ``*.log``
# to the daemon as the build context ‚Äî bloating the context tarball
# to 1GB+ and risking secret leakage (``dev.db`` contains user data,
# ``.env.local`` may contain real API keys).
#
# This file mirrors the patterns from the root .dockerignore but adds
# frontend-specific patterns (Next.js build artifacts, Prisma backups,
# the local SQLite dev DB).
#
# Frontend Dockerfile (frontend/Dockerfile) only COPYs:
#   - frontend/package.json
#   - frontend/package-lock.json
#   - frontend/bun.lock (optional)
#   - frontend/ (the source tree)
# So everything else here is excluded from the build context.

# Node modules ‚Äî NEVER in the build context. The Dockerfile runs
# ``npm ci`` or ``bun install`` inside the image.
node_modules
node_modules/**

# Next.js build artifacts ‚Äî NEVER in the build context. The Dockerfile
# runs ``next build`` inside the image. Shipping local ``.next/`` causes
# non-reproducible builds (stale local state affects the image).
.next
.next/**

# Next.js standalone output (generated by ``next build``)
.out
out/**

# Tests and test artifacts ‚Äî NEVER in production images.
tests
tests/**
__tests__
__tests__/**
*.test.ts
*.test.tsx
*.test.js
*.spec.ts
*.spec.tsx
*.spec.js
coverage
coverage/**
.nyc_output

# Backups and uploaded code ‚Äî NEVER in production images.
# These directories accumulate dev artifacts (old Prisma schemas,
# uploaded user code samples, etc.) and should NEVER ship to a registry.
uploaded_code
uploaded_code/**
src_backup
src_backup/**
prisma_backup
prisma_backup/**
public_backup
public_backup/**

# Local SQLite databases ‚Äî NEVER in production images.
# ``dev.db`` contains real user data from local testing (emails, hashed
# passwords). Shipping it to a registry is a data-leak finding.
*.db
*.db-journal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# Logs ‚Äî NEVER in production images.
*.log
*.log.*
logs
logs/**

# IDE / editor config ‚Äî never needed inside a container.
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store

# Version control ‚Äî never needed inside a container.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Local env files ‚Äî NEVER in production images.
# ``.env.local`` may contain real API keys (Resend, Stripe, etc.).
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.env

# TypeScript build info ‚Äî generated artifact, not source.
*.tsbuildinfo

# Tooling configs that are not needed at build time.
.eslintignore
.prettierignore
.prettierrc
.stylelintrc
jest.config.js
playwright.config.ts
